    <releaseNotes>
      ### Added
      - New option to close PolyMC after launch
      - Now detects Java from environment
      - New `Open page &amp; copy code` button in MSA login dialog
      - Added StartupWMClass to .desktop file so DEs can behave
      - Added PolyMC news
      - Added CurseForge and Modrinth mod downloader
      - New CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license for PolyMC logos and branding
      - Added MSA-Client-ID override in UI
      - Added missing tooltip for instance export
      - Added MSA Client ID change detection and prompt
      - Added Matrix space link

      ### Changed
      - Default to the system locale on first startup
      - Replaced `paste.ee` with `0x0.st` and `paste.polymc.org`
      - Updated information in the About dialog
      - Migrated to upstream QuaZip 1.2
      - QuaZip is now linked statically
      - Internal libraries are now linked statically
      - PolyMC specific translations now hosted on weblate
      - Update metadata
      - Version string now shows the branch that PolyMC was built from
      - New MSA Client ID
      - Replace old build layout system with new `Launcher_PORTABLE` cmake flag
      - Reorganized icon themes
      - [Windows] Now runs on WSL
      - [macOS] Move app data to `Application Support`

      ### Fixed
      - Add some logging to profile fetching failures
      - Ignore invalid lines altogether in java checker
      - Correctly set http status code in auth reply
      - Log server response when failing to fetch profile
      - Fix error message
      - Fixed inconsistent behavior of icons when exiting the settings screen
      - Fixed freedesktop icons
      - [macOS] Fixed GUI identifier

      ### Removed
      - Removed MultiMC news
      - Removed legacy instance support

      **Full Changelog**: https://github.com/PolyMC/PolyMC/compare/1.0.6...1.1.0
</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
